mployers include other healthcare providers, including Swedish  American and Saint Francis Hospitals.  The information on this site will help you get settled, learn about the city, and find something  exciting to do or see, including Rockford’s well-known movie theatres.   Take some time to browse through the information contained there, and  you will find information about things like the Burpee Museum of Natural History and the Anderson Japanese Garden .  If you’re interested in the culinary options of Rockford, you can visit the Restaurants section of their website. Here you can find all the information that you’ll need about local favorites.   xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-16"? Skip Nav UICOIS Navigation Menu Home About OIS Students Prospective Students Admitted Students Current Students Forms Academics F-1 Student Employment J-1 Student Employment Travel Replacement of Documents Address Updates Change of Status Departure Extension Scholarships Peoria Rockford Incoming Exchange Students Fulbright Foreign Student and Scholar (Non U.S. Citizens) Faculty, Staff, and Scholars Visitors Departments Programs Life in Illinois Alumni Resources News   Office of International Services 1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 996-3121 Email: ois@uic.edu Facebook Instagram Twitter Copyright ©  2018 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois | Web Privacy Statement Cookie Settings    